nd the presence of qualifying injuries or damages. [Data: Entities (103), Relationships (215, 274, 275, 396, 397, 398, +more)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"AUTOMOBILE DEATH INDEMNITY INSURANCE COVERAGE as a key benefit\",\n            \"explanation\": \"AUTOMOBILE DEATH INDEMNITY INSURANCE COVERAGE is a specific benefit provided by Allstate that pays a benefit if an insured person dies within 90 days of an auto accident, or within one year if the injury prevents them from working. This benefit is directly tied to the occurrence of an AUTO ACCIDENT and is activated when death results from injuries sustained in the incident. The benefit amount is specified in the POLICY DECLARATIONS, indicating that it is a formally documented and quantifiable component of the policy. This coverage provides financial support to beneficiaries in the event of a fatal accident, reflecting the policy’s emphasis on post-accident protection. [Data: Entities (212), Relationships (366)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"BODILY INJURY as a prerequisite for multiple benefits\",\n            \"explanation\": \"BODILY INJURY is a critical element in the claims process, serving as a prerequisite for medical payments coverage, disability benefits, and death indemnity claims. It is defined as physical harm or trauma sustained by a person as a direct consequence of an auto accident. The presence of bodily injury triggers the activation of specific coverage provisions, including immediate medical payments regardless of fault. The severity of the injury determines the scope of benefits, with continuous total disability or death within one year of the incident qualifying for disability income or death benefits. Liability limits apply to the total amount payable for bodily injury sustained by one or more individuals in a single accident. [Data: Relationships (215)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"SICKNESS and DISEASE as covered consequences 