mits, and conditions of the policy, and it serves as the authoritative source for determining the financial value of benefits. The relationship between the death indemnity benefit and the policy declarations ensures that claim amounts are standardized and transparent. This linkage is essential for both insurers and policyholders to understand the scope of financial protection available. [Data: Relationships (366)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Coverage scope limited to public roads and covered vehicles\",\n            \"explanation\": \"The policy’s coverage is strictly limited to incidents involving motor vehicles, trailers, or semi-trailers operating on public roads. This restriction ensures that only accidents occurring in the context of public transportation are eligible for benefits. Vehicles used off public roads, such as off-road vehicles, are excluded unless they are temporarily on public roads. Similarly, vehicles used as residences are not covered, even if they are involved in an accident. This limitation reflects the policy’s focus on standard road-based motor vehicle incidents and helps manage risk exposure. [Data: Entities (103, 248, 249), Relationships (397, 398)]\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Medical payments coverage activated regardless of fault\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Medical payments coverage is activated immediately upon an AUTO ACCIDENT, regardless of fault. This provision is designed to provide prompt financial support for medical treatment, reducing the burden on injured parties during recovery. It applies to injuries resulting from the accident and is not contingent on liability determination. This coverage is a key component of the policy’s commitment to immediate assistance and reflects a no-fault approach to medical cost reimbursement. It ensures that injured individuals can access necessary care without delay, even if the insured is at fault. [Data: Entities (103), Relationships (21